            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " A Cd-filter was used to eliminate the neutrons of",
                "previous bursts."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Two discs of metallic rhodium with thickness of",
                " 3.37E-04 at/b and 1.87E-03 at/b - for transmission.",
                " 1.87E-03 at/b thick metallic Rh-103 disc -for capture."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " Capture experiments, the flight path was 14.5 m.",
                " Fixed Bi and Na 'black' resonance filters were used to",
                " reduce gamma background from source and background",
                " could be monitored using 'black' resonance minima at",
                " 802. eV and 2.85 keV."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Transmission experiments, flight path was 50 m.",
                " Background was measured at 'black' resonances of",
                " permanent filters of Cd, Au, Co and Na placed in",
                " neutron beam.Signal to background ratio 85:1 at 4.9eV,",
                " 115:1 at 130 eV, 30:1 at 2.85 keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "45-RH-103(N,0),,EN",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "45-RH-103(N,0),,EN",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "45-RH-103(N,0)",
                        "target": "45-RH-103",
                        "projectile": "N",
                        "process": "0",
                        "product": "",
                        "quantity": ",EN",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",EN"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  The data have been normalized",
                "    to the well-isolated and saturated Rh-103",
                "    resonance at 1.26-eV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For the capture measurements-two C(6)D(6)",
                "  liquid scintillators NE230 of 10.0-cm diameter",
                "  and 7.5 cm height, placed at 90-degree with respect",
                "  to the direction of the neutron beam;"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The shape of the neutron spectrum was measured",
                "  with a double Frisch-gridded ionization chamber",
                "  with two back-to-back layers of 43.5 microgram/cm**2",
                "  Boron-10 each."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GLASD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For the transmission measurements -",
                "  The neutrons were detected by 6-mm-thick NE912",
                "  Li-6 glass scintillator;"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Two BF3   proportional counters were used to",
                "  monitor the stability of the accelerator and to",
                "  normalize the spectra to the total neutron intensity."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Corrections for self-shielding in the ionization",
                " chamber, and for the difference in neutron flux at the",
                " target positions, and for the ionization chamber were",
                " carried out. Maximum dead-time correction for the",
                " capture measurements are 10%. Correction to dead time",
                "less 1.25% below 2.85 keV for transmission measurement.",
                " Correction for background."
              ]
            }
          ],
